claim.claim-text:
1. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor device, the method comprising:
heating an organic source in an evaporator to provide a source gas on a substrate;
pumping the source gas, a derived molecule, and air through an exhaust line connected to a chamber;
using an analyzer to detect the derived molecule, the analyzer being connected to the exhaust line; and
determining whether or not a partial pressure of the derived molecule is equal to or greater than a reference partial pressure.
